  "texts": [
    "Interpretation of PAGs is rather more difficult given that edge types can have several meanings.",
    "Generally speaking, causal inference applications (Noguiera et al. 2022) require a BN model with a well-defined DAG to be able to do causal inference.",
    "Incorporation of human knowledge either before the learning process, during the learning process (active learning) or by orientating undirected edges in the CPDAG can help In some cases, a practitioner's aim may be to identify the major causal effects rather than try to learn a complete causal graph.",
    "Here, approaches such as those provided by the BiDAG package which produce a sample of the most probable graphs may be useful.",
    "Model averaging over the sample graphs allow the most probable examples of features such as arcs or Markov Blankets to be identified."
  ],
